    "v1": "Wilt thou, O man, live happily, And dwell with God eternally, The ten commandments keep, for thus Our God Himself biddeth us. Kyr&#39; eleison!",
    "v2": "I am the Lord and God! take heed No other god doth thee mislead; Thy heart shall trust alone in Me, My kingdom then thou shalt be.",
    "v3": "Honor My Name in word and deed, And call on Me in time of need: Hallow the Sabbath, that I may Work in thy heart on that day.",
    "v4": "Obedient always, next to Me, To father and to mother be; Kill no man: even anger dread; Keep sacred thy marriage bed.",
    "v5": "Steal not, nor do thy neighbor wrong By bearing witness with false tongue; Thy neighbor&#39;s wife desire thou not, Nor grudge him aught he hath got."
  },
